prompt: Summarize the following story in first person: My supervisor suggested lets go for a roller coaster ride. I have heard so much about  the roller coaster and i'm dying to try it. I said no  way i wont be scared to death. I protested  shaking my  head but my boss would not let me. Everyone else and  friends at work greed to .   I  had no  choice to give  in.   I followed him unwillingly,   i was even more nervous when i saw  the CAUTION.  We entered  into  a room where we were directed and our seats shwn to us. I  SHUT my eyes seized both the seats so tightly that they ached. i heard people shouting excitedly, finally the  roller coaster moved.  slowly first then faster  and began  to pick up speed.  I felt my stomach turning upside down' my heart  was pounding  loudly i regretted  taking the ride on this scary thing. i screamed at the top of my voice  and my hair was flying widely in the air. it really drove me nuts,but everyone seemed exited  on  the  roller  coaster.
